('Grammar and Structure', 'Verb Form', 'has increased', 'The number of complaints _____ dramatically this quarter.', 'has increased', 'have increased', 'increased', 'increases', '\"The number\" is singular and requires singular verb.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Verb Form', 'rains', 'If it _____ tomorrow, the outdoor ceremony will be canceled.', 'rains', 'rained', 'will rain', 'would rain', 'First conditional: present simple in if-clause for real possibilities.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Verb Form', 'had been investigating', 'The detectives _____ the case for months before finding new evidence.', 'had been investigating', 'investigated', 'have investigated', 'were investigating', 'Past perfect continuous for ongoing action completed before another past action.'),
